White 1 is creative. However, when black plays at 2, white cannot create a completely dead shape, and merely adds extra stones as a sacrifice.

When black captures white at 4, even if white makes one eye false with 5, black can resist at 6, starting a pae. It was a fantastically energetic attack, but in the end it fails.

The reason it is classed as a failure is because in this case there is a way to capture black unconditionally.
